 32  /-- `sqrt n` is the square root of a natural number `n`. If `n` is not a
 33    perfect square, it returns the largest `k:ℕ` such that `k*k ≤ n`. -/
 34  def sqrt (n : ℕ) : ℕ :=
id                 ┴    ┴
src                ┴    ┴
typ                ┴    ┴
 35  match size n with
id         └──┘ ┴
src        └──┘
typ        └──┘ ┴
 36  | 0      := 0
 37  | succ s := sqrt_aux (shiftl 1 (bit0 (div2 s))) 0 n
id     └──┘ ┴    └──────┘  └────┘    └──┘  └──┘        ┴
src    └──┘      └──────┘  └────┘    └──┘  └──┘
typ    └──┘ ┴    └──────┘  └────┘    └──┘  └──┘        ┴
 38  end
